      "message": "I assume that you don\u0027t intend to change the external interface of any of the variants of ScopedPtr, including this one.  And that you want all these to treat T the same way.  But this change seems like it does do such a change (albeit in an unlikely circumstance).  If wanted to have a \n\nScopedCustomPtr\u003cint*, \u003c...func that takes an int**\u003e\u003e\n\nthat is, a scoped pointer to a pointer-sized cell containing a pointer to int, then I could no longer create that: the remove_pointer would cause this to be a scoped pointer to a T, not a T*.\n\nThis seems undesirable -- unique_ptr, for example, doesn\u0027t do this, AFAIK.  So maybe investigating David\u0027s suggestion for fixing the motivating nullptr annoyance would be worthwhile.",
